[[Image:Ashraful.png|thumb|85px|right|[[Mohammad Ashraful]]]]
This is a list of all men and boys who have captained a '''Bangladeshi national cricket team''' at the official international level. [[Bangladeshi cricket team|Bangladesh]] became a full member of the [[International Cricket Council]] on [[26 June]] [[2000]], and played its first [[Test cricket|Test match]] shortly afterwards. Before then, it had been an associate member of the ICC since 1977, competing in five [[ICC Trophy|ICC Trophies]], the leading one-day competition for non-Test nations. Bangladesh has not had a good start to their Test record, winning only once since admission to Test status, and that was against a weakened [[Zimbabwean cricket team|Zimbabwe]]. 

Bangladesh do not play [[Women's Test cricket]] or [[Women's one-day international cricket]]. 

==Men's cricket==
===Test match captains===
This is a list of cricketers who have [[captain (cricket)|captained]] the [[Bangladeshi cricket team|Bangladesh cricket team]] for at least one [[Test cricket|Test match]].

Only five men have captained Bangladesh at Test level.

