===Men's One-Day International captains===

This is a list of cricketers who have [[captain (cricket)|captained]] the [[Bangladeshi cricket team]] for at least one [[One Day International]]. Where a player has a dagger (<U+2020>) next to an ODI match series in which he captained at least one ODI, that denotes that player was captain for a minor proportion in a series. Bangladesh's greatest ODI victory was beating [[Australian cricket team|Australia]] on [[18 June]] [[2005]]. Other teams they have beaten are [[Pakistani cricket team|Pakistan]] and [[Scottish cricket team|Scotland]] (both in the [[1999 Cricket World Cup]]), [[Kenyan cricket team|Kenya]] in 1998/9, [[Zimbabwean cricket team|Zimbabwe]] (once in 2003/4, three times in 2004/5), [[Indian cricket team|India]] (once in 2004/5, once in the [[2007 Cricket World Cup]]), [[Sri Lankan cricket team|Sri Lanka]] (once in [[Sri Lankan cricket team in Bangladesh in 2005-06|2005/6]]) and [[South African cricket team|South Africa]] (once in the [[2007 Cricket World Cup]]).

